1
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:24,420
♪It's a sordid story that you've made♪

2
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:32,700
♪Up to fill my mind with doubts and pain♪

3
00:00:34,780 --> 00:00:40,220
♪Blood I shed, and tears I wept,
are you satisfied?♪

4
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:42,540
♪Enjoying what's mine♪

5
00:00:42,540 --> 00:00:49,500
♪Have you found a way
to bury guilt and shame♪

6
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:55,020
♪I'm coming back to life♪

7
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Through the seven gates of death♪

8
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:02,820
♪I'm coming back survived♪

9
00:01:02,820 --> 00:01:06,580
♪Feeling great to see you fall♪

10
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:10,820
♪I'm taking back what's mine♪

11
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:15,340
♪Bringing horror to the battlefield♪

12
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:19,060
♪Lay it to waste♪

13
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:22,940
♪Til the day my kingdom is reclaimed♪

14
00:01:38,260 --> 00:01:42,540
=Her Blaze=

15
00:01:43,260 --> 00:01:45,780
=Episode 18=

16
00:01:53,719 --> 00:01:54,519
Grandmother.

17
00:02:05,180 --> 00:02:08,140
(Two months later)

18
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:19,599
Sit for a while.

19
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,080
Bougainvillea.

20
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:36,080
This was my mother's favorite flower.

21
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,400
When I was little,

22
00:02:40,879 --> 00:02:42,120
my mother told me

23
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,520
this flower

24
00:02:44,759 --> 00:02:45,919
didn't need much watering

25
00:02:45,919 --> 00:02:47,680
to bloom beautifully.

26
00:02:48,719 --> 00:02:50,080
At that time, I thought

27
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,280
she simply

28
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,400
liked this flower.

29
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,439
Thinking back on it later,

30
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:57,919
I think she was envious.

31
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,159
Envious of how wild

32
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,159
and strong it could be.

33
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:12,599
Perhaps only when someone

34
00:03:12,599 --> 00:03:14,439
faces a truly complete loss

35
00:03:15,919 --> 00:03:17,990
will they have the courage
to find their inner self.

36
00:03:19,719 --> 00:03:21,280
Your mother has always loved you.

37
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,000
At least since you were hospitalized,

38
00:03:24,319 --> 00:03:25,759
I feel she has changed a lot.

39
00:03:27,039 --> 00:03:28,080
She's been quite strong.

40
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,560
I know she loves me.

41
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,400
Maybe in the past,

42
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,560
I was always

43
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,879
avoiding these issues.

44
00:03:45,039 --> 00:03:46,159
Growing up,

45
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,919
I always felt my mother was weak,

46
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,719
while my father was very strict.

47
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,120
What puzzles me most

48
00:03:54,719 --> 00:03:55,520
is that my dad

49
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,919
(Five years ago)
seemed to have

50
00:03:56,919 --> 00:03:58,240
(Five years ago)
an inexplicable loathing for me.

51
00:03:58,439 --> 00:03:59,159
If you like them,

52
00:03:59,159 --> 00:04:00,360
I'll buy them every day.

53
00:04:00,719 --> 00:04:01,800
Thank you.

54
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,680
Come over for dinner often.

55
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,520
Treat this place like your own home.

56
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:08,319
Yuci, come and eat.

57
00:04:08,319 --> 00:04:09,120
Coming.

58
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,479
Liangliang,

59
00:04:11,919 --> 00:04:14,680
I prepared a gift for you to celebrate
passing your thesis defense.

60
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,400
Really?

61
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:16,800
Take a look.

62
00:04:17,439 --> 00:04:18,560
A commemorative album.

63
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:23,600
Didn't you say you
weren't coming home for dinner?

64
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,279
Be quiet.

65
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,439
Explain this to me.

66
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:29,959
Why didn't you participate
in the bank's campus recruitment?

67
00:04:30,439 --> 00:04:31,160
It's a good job.

68
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,279
Why did you reject it?

69
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,079
Why, Yuci?

70
00:04:36,580 --> 00:04:38,519
What Liangliang said
the other day reminded me.

71
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,160
I don't want others to arrange my life.

72
00:04:40,170 --> 00:04:42,450
I also want to apply
for Professor Han's graduate program.

73
00:04:42,639 --> 00:04:44,439
Can you really
compare yourself to others?

74
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:45,439
Don't you know

75
00:04:45,439 --> 00:04:46,839
what your own personality is like?

76
00:04:46,839 --> 00:04:49,000
In all these years,
when have you ever listened to me?

77
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:50,480
I want you to work at the bank

78
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,120
so you can adapt to society
as soon as possible,

79
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,720
not so you can stay home every day

80
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,439
writing unrealistic things!

81
00:04:55,439 --> 00:04:56,759
I want to live the life I want.

82
00:04:56,759 --> 00:04:58,040
How is that unrealistic?

83
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:00,390
- Who do you think you're talking to?
-  I'm talking to you.

84
00:05:00,439 --> 00:05:01,360
Mom, I'm not eating.

85
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:02,600
Yuci.

86
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,399
Yuci!

87
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:05,639
Who said you could leave?

88
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:07,759
Mr. Rao, please calm down.

89
00:05:07,839 --> 00:05:09,199
I'll go talk to Yuci.

90
00:05:13,399 --> 00:05:14,839
What are you doing?

91
00:05:14,839 --> 00:05:15,879
Why get so angry?

92
00:05:15,879 --> 00:05:16,959
Just talk it through.

93
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:19,839
Yuci,

94
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:22,480
it's been so many years.

95
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,759
Why is it still like this?

96
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,040
I don't know either.

97
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,879
Are you like this with your father?

98
00:05:35,399 --> 00:05:36,399
Not really.

99
00:05:39,399 --> 00:05:41,240
Do you think a father could

100
00:05:42,959 --> 00:05:43,759
be born with

101
00:05:43,759 --> 00:05:45,079
a loathing for his own daughter?

102
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:47,959
Ever since I was little,

103
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,480
he has always hated me.

104
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:53,959
I'm wondering

105
00:05:56,959 --> 00:05:57,920
if we were enemies

106
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,240
in a past life.

107
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,000
Although I helped my dad

108
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,279
pay off his debts last time,

109
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:11,279
the knot in our relationship

110
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,319
has never been untied.

111
00:06:15,079 --> 00:06:16,199
Sooner or later,

112
00:06:17,279 --> 00:06:18,720
I'll need Rao Shusheng

113
00:06:20,759 --> 00:06:21,959
to give me an answer.

114
00:06:28,439 --> 00:06:29,240
Rao Yuci.

115
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,200
It's time to change your dressing.

116
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:40,199
How are you?

117
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,000
I'm fine now.

118
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,519
I've almost recovered.

119
00:06:44,639 --> 00:06:46,360
I can be discharged next week.

120
00:06:46,839 --> 00:06:47,839
So you're fine.

121
00:06:48,519 --> 00:06:49,319
Rao Yuci,

122
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:50,959
I'm telling you,

123
00:06:50,959 --> 00:06:53,480
if something like this happens again,
you have to call me.

124
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,839
At the very least,
I can pretty much guarantee

125
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:57,560
that it won't be us in the hospital.

126
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,160
The joke didn't land.

127
00:07:06,079 --> 00:07:06,879
That's okay.

128
00:07:06,879 --> 00:07:08,600
Laughing too hard
might rip your stitches.

129
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,759
It's all in the past.

130
00:07:11,759 --> 00:07:13,160
How is everyone?

131
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,519
They're fine.

132
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,160
Wang Meng is on maternity leave.

133
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:18,040
The other two wanted to come,
but I stopped them

134
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,570
because I didn't want them
to disturb your rest.

135
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,639
Want to hear some gossip?

136
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:25,160
Lysen has been quite lively
since you were gone.

137
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,120
Miss Gao

138
00:07:29,399 --> 00:07:31,399
helped Bai Liangliang install a bug

139
00:07:31,399 --> 00:07:32,519
in Jiang Dongchao's office.

140
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,519
Later, she was fired

141
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,199
and taken away by the police,

142
00:07:36,199 --> 00:07:37,290
detained for several days.

143
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,720
Jiang Dongchao has gained

144
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,519
the approval of several shareholders

145
00:07:41,279 --> 00:07:42,639
and is preparing to acquire Bosi.

146
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:47,360
What about Bai Liangliang?

147
00:07:48,399 --> 00:07:49,199
Bai Liangliang

148
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:52,279
disappeared after you were hospitalized.

149
00:07:53,199 --> 00:07:54,600
No one knows where she went.

150
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,480
Ms. Ren, do you still want this?

151
00:08:04,639 --> 00:08:06,199
An old friend has returned, though.

152
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,360
Chen Xi.

153
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,000
Mr. Jiang,

154
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,079
I'm back.

155
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:33,240
Chen Xi is now in charge
of the PR Department

156
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:35,230
and is temporarily managing Dept 1.

157
00:08:36,879 --> 00:08:37,960
To Mr. Jiang,

158
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:38,799
Chen Xi is the least

159
00:08:38,799 --> 00:08:39,879
threatening of them all.

160
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:41,480
But

161
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:44,799
she's targeting Dept 3.

162
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,759
You need to decide
what you're going to do.

163
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:53,559
Bai Muran is dead.

164
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:56,720
The police ruled it a suicide
out of fear of punishment.

165
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,759
The police came to see me.

166
00:09:01,559 --> 00:09:03,720
I told them everything

167
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:06,360
about how he manipulated
the market to defraud Li Qiang.

168
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,159
It's all over.

169
00:09:11,399 --> 00:09:12,559
Is it really over?

170
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,039
You should know,

171
00:09:16,879 --> 00:09:17,840
Bai Qingyu is not

172
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,080
an easy person to deal with.

173
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:22,399
This matter will find its way

174
00:09:23,039 --> 00:09:24,200
back to you sooner or later.

175
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:26,879
I just want to return

176
00:09:26,879 --> 00:09:28,120
everything they did to me

177
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:31,759
back to them.

178
00:09:33,759 --> 00:09:34,919
But you must realize,

179
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,639
given the current relationship

180
00:09:37,639 --> 00:09:39,230
between Jiang Dongchao and Bai Qingyu,

181
00:09:40,039 --> 00:09:42,200
Lysen will most likely not side with you.

182
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:43,879
I know.

183
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,240
Ms. Ren.

184
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:59,120
Didn't expect that I would
come back, did you?

185
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:01,440
At Lysen,

186
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,480
people come and go

187
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,399
every single day.

188
00:10:04,039 --> 00:10:05,680
How could I possibly
care about everyone?

189
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:08,879
The point is, how long can you stay
after coming back?

190
00:10:10,879 --> 00:10:11,679
By the way,

191
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:14,279
Lysen's shareholder appreciation meeting
is about to start.

192
00:10:14,279 --> 00:10:15,960
As the PR Director,

193
00:10:16,559 --> 00:10:18,440
is Mr. Jiang's speech script ready yet?

194
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,120
Good job.

195
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,360
Ms. Ren, do you think

196
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,919
Rao Yuci will come back?

197
00:10:27,759 --> 00:10:29,919
Since Rao Yuci and Bai Liangliang
are both gone,

198
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:31,080
I think

199
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:33,120
it's time for you to make new friends.

200
00:10:33,559 --> 00:10:35,799
For example, me.

201
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,399
Wait a moment.

202
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,240
Ms. Chen.

203
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:52,360
Give those to me.

204
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,639
You can clock out now.

205
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:54,759
All right, Ms. Chen.

206
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,480
What are you doing up here?

207
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:19,600
This is Mr. Jiang's speech script
for the day after tomorrow.

208
00:11:20,399 --> 00:11:21,639
I brought it over for you.

209
00:11:25,799 --> 00:11:27,399
Just email it to me next time.

210
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:35,759
Chen,

211
00:12:37,559 --> 00:12:38,840
thank you for staying

212
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,879
by her side these past three months.

213
00:12:41,279 --> 00:12:42,120
It's thanks to you.

214
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,600
Don't mention it, Mrs. Rao.

215
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:44,679
It's what I should do.

216
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,159
There's something weighing

217
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,759
on my mind.

218
00:12:52,879 --> 00:12:54,320
I'd like to talk to you about it

219
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:56,480
and hear your opinion.

220
00:12:57,519 --> 00:12:58,320
Sure.

221
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:06,519
I think Yuci

222
00:13:08,039 --> 00:13:09,039
must be

223
00:13:11,559 --> 00:13:14,000
utterly disappointed in me in her heart.

224
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:17,000
I left her in the treatment center

225
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,320
for so long.

226
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,039
I can't even imagine

227
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,600
how much she suffered.

228
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,519
So after she got out

229
00:13:27,519 --> 00:13:28,679
of the treatment center,

230
00:13:30,399 --> 00:13:31,919
she wasn't willing to come home.

231
00:13:33,039 --> 00:13:34,360
I can understand that.

232
00:13:35,639 --> 00:13:36,720
But this time,

233
00:13:37,559 --> 00:13:39,000
after she was injured,

234
00:13:41,559 --> 00:13:44,000
she hasn't been willing
to say a single word to me.

235
00:13:44,519 --> 00:13:45,919
As her mother,

236
00:13:48,039 --> 00:13:49,159
I've been too incompetent

237
00:13:49,919 --> 00:13:51,000
and too weak.

238
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:55,159
Mrs. Rao, has Yuci ever cried
in front of you?

239
00:13:56,559 --> 00:13:57,639
I saw it once.

240
00:14:00,159 --> 00:14:01,360
At the entrance of Lysen,

241
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:03,879
her dad hit her in public.

242
00:14:06,919 --> 00:14:08,200
When did this happen?

243
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:10,799
Not long after she got out
of the treatment center.

244
00:14:11,759 --> 00:14:13,080
I had no idea.

245
00:14:15,399 --> 00:14:17,840
Her dad has gone too far.

246
00:14:21,639 --> 00:14:23,600
Yuci has always been
in pain because of this.

247
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,279
From a professional perspective,

248
00:14:26,570 --> 00:14:28,870
this was also one of the reasons
why she fell ill before.

249
00:14:29,879 --> 00:14:31,159
She just wanted to understand

250
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,960
why her own father

251
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:37,120
could be so heartless to her.

252
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:40,799
I want to help Yuci resolve this issue.

253
00:14:42,559 --> 00:14:43,600
Perhaps that's the only way

254
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:47,000
she can truly come home.

255
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:57,279
Actually,

256
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,120
Yuci was supposed to have

257
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:01,279
a sibling.

258
00:15:03,039 --> 00:15:05,080
But we've always kept it from her.

259
00:15:05,759 --> 00:15:09,399
Her dad doesn't hate her.

260
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,399
He's actually terrified of her.

261
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:14,120
A while back,

262
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:15,960
when her dad was hospitalized,

263
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:17,799
he kept muttering

264
00:15:17,799 --> 00:15:20,240
about the terrifying past.

265
00:15:20,559 --> 00:15:21,360
It's her.

266
00:15:23,159 --> 00:15:23,960
It's her.

267
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:27,919
It's her.

268
00:15:29,559 --> 00:15:31,000
She shouldn't have survived.

269
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,039
Yunian.

270
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,039
If the one who survived was Yunian,

271
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:44,039
it definitely wouldn't be like it is now.

272
00:15:47,039 --> 00:15:47,840
Doctor,

273
00:15:48,559 --> 00:15:50,039
what's happening to him?

274
00:15:50,799 --> 00:15:52,480
He may have suffered a severe shock.

275
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:53,759
The blood vessels were blocked,

276
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:55,840
which led to a cerebral infarction.

277
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,720
He's currently in a delirious state.

278
00:15:57,919 --> 00:15:59,399
He is not fully conscious yet.

279
00:16:03,559 --> 00:16:04,360
Yunian.

280
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,159
Yunian.

281
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,000
Yunian.

282
00:16:14,740 --> 00:16:17,620
(Thirty years ago)

283
00:16:18,039 --> 00:16:20,200
(May 2, 1994)
(Found out my wife is having twins.)

284
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,080
(I'm in a great mood today.)

285
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,480
(I want to name one child)

286
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,720
(Yunian,)

287
00:16:24,759 --> 00:16:26,759
(and the other child Yuci.)

288
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,080
(I'm excited and nervous.)

289
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:31,080
(I hope these two babies can grow up)

290
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:32,519
(supporting each other.)

291
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,000
Look.

292
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:36,159
This, this...

293
00:16:36,159 --> 00:16:37,120
These light spots

294
00:16:37,519 --> 00:16:38,919
are all signs of bleeding.

295
00:16:43,340 --> 00:16:45,140
(Ultrasound: Fetus 2 is underdeveloped.)

296
00:16:46,679 --> 00:16:47,480
Doctor,

297
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,639
what does this mean?

298
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,279
I don't quite understand.

299
00:16:51,759 --> 00:16:52,919
Simply put,

300
00:16:52,919 --> 00:16:55,120
this is a very rare medical condition.

301
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:56,480
Because the twins

302
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:57,720
share a single placenta,

303
00:16:58,360 --> 00:16:59,120
the two fetuses

304
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:01,039
should absorb nutrients very evenly

305
00:17:01,279 --> 00:17:02,360
and then grow rapidly

306
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,399
inside the mother.

307
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,200
But the current situation is that

308
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:07,880
one child is at a normal fetal level,

309
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:08,799
while the other

310
00:17:08,799 --> 00:17:10,279
is pathologically small.

311
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,359
In other words,

312
00:17:11,359 --> 00:17:13,599
one child is absorbing nutrients
too quickly,

313
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:15,599
robbing the other child of their nutrition

314
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:17,400
and causing the other fetus

315
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,480
to gradually wither.

316
00:17:18,799 --> 00:17:19,599
Eventually...

317
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:20,720
Eventually?

318
00:17:22,039 --> 00:17:23,039
Are you saying

319
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:24,440
that one of my children

320
00:17:24,519 --> 00:17:25,440
in the womb

321
00:17:25,559 --> 00:17:27,119
is absorbing the other child?

322
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:28,880
I understand

323
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,000
how you're feeling right now.

324
00:17:30,559 --> 00:17:31,400
To be honest,

325
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,000
in my decades of practice,

326
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,990
this is also the first time
I've encountered such a case.

327
00:17:35,279 --> 00:17:36,200
But this situation

328
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:38,559
does indeed exist in medicine.

329
00:17:39,039 --> 00:17:40,160
(June 3, 1994)
(Today I received)

330
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,160
(shocking news)

331
00:17:41,279 --> 00:17:42,720
(from the doctor.)

332
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,160
(One of my children)

333
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,000
(is slowly)

334
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,559
(absorbing the other.)

335
00:17:46,759 --> 00:17:48,400
(Because Zhaohe's carrying twins,)

336
00:17:48,410 --> 00:17:50,350
(she has already
developed gestational diabetes.)

337
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:51,240
(Therefore,)

338
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:53,000
(I don't dare tell her about this.)

339
00:17:53,039 --> 00:17:54,440
(I can only keep this bad news)

340
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:55,599
(to myself)

341
00:17:55,799 --> 00:17:56,960
(and bear it alone.)

342
00:17:58,420 --> 00:18:06,160
(Operating Room)

343
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:07,880
Congratulations! It's a girl.

344
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,359
Here, hold her and take a look.

345
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:17,759
Nurse,

346
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:21,519
is this a birthmark?

347
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:22,960
Not exactly.

348
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,079
Wasn't there

349
00:18:24,079 --> 00:18:25,400
another one in the womb before?

350
00:18:25,519 --> 00:18:26,680
This is the mark

351
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:28,160
from when that child was absorbed.

352
00:18:28,319 --> 00:18:30,119
It usually fades as she grows up.

353
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,480
Hello?

354
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:42,039
Hello, Shusheng?

355
00:18:42,759 --> 00:18:43,839
Hurry back home.

356
00:18:43,839 --> 00:18:45,160
Your mother is dying!

357
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:56,000
(January 15, 1995)
(Today my daughter was born.)

358
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:57,480
(Almost at the same time,)

359
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:59,359
(my mother passed away.)

360
00:18:59,519 --> 00:19:01,519
(My father was grief-stricken,)

361
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:03,720
(even appearing
exceptionally indifferent)

362
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:05,640
(toward the arrival
of his granddaughter.)

363
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:18,039
(May 14, 2012)
(The factory caught fire last night.)

364
00:19:18,559 --> 00:19:20,039
(Two workers were burned to death.)

365
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,480
(The goods and equipment
in the warehouse)

366
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:23,720
(were also destroyed.)

367
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:26,000
(One coincidence after another.)

368
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,079
(The relatives are all saying)

369
00:19:28,839 --> 00:19:30,240
(it was brought on by our daughter.)

370
00:19:34,359 --> 00:19:35,240
These things

371
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:38,559
have been hidden in our hearts
for a long time.

372
00:19:40,039 --> 00:19:41,880
I've never dared to tell Yuci.

373
00:19:44,279 --> 00:19:45,960
I'm afraid of hurting her.

374
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:47,519
Mrs. Rao,

375
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:48,920
don't blame yourself.

376
00:19:50,519 --> 00:19:51,839
Now that Yuci has returned

377
00:19:51,839 --> 00:19:52,960
from the brink of death,

378
00:19:53,759 --> 00:19:55,279
let the past be the past.

379
00:19:56,319 --> 00:19:57,839
The most important thing now

380
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,799
is trying to understand Yuci.

381
00:20:03,079 --> 00:20:04,799
Mrs. Rao, Yuci is fragile.

382
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:06,680
Regarding those past events,

383
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,920
you must not let Yuci know.

384
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:10,960
She might not be able to handle it.

385
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,000
Yuci,

386
00:20:40,519 --> 00:20:41,279
I've made

387
00:20:41,279 --> 00:20:42,759
some delicious food for you.

388
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:50,000
Come on, be careful.

389
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:55,519
Look.

390
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:57,759
Scrambled eggs with tomatoes.

391
00:21:00,039 --> 00:21:02,000
And look, sautéed celery with shrimp.

392
00:21:07,039 --> 00:21:08,240
Eat more.

393
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:10,039
That's how you'll recover well.

394
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:12,039
Here.

395
00:21:27,559 --> 00:21:28,359
This.

396
00:21:28,559 --> 00:21:31,359
Lately, staying with you in the hospital

397
00:21:31,359 --> 00:21:32,440
reminded me

398
00:21:32,759 --> 00:21:33,960
of when I was in the hospital

399
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,039
giving birth to you.

400
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:36,240
Look.

401
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,640
This was from
your one-month celebration.

402
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,279
Chubby and adorable.

403
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:46,000
And look at this
little pillow you slept on.

404
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,160
I sewed it myself, stitch by stitch,

405
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:50,119
back when I was pregnant with you.

406
00:21:51,519 --> 00:21:52,480
In the blink of an eye,

407
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:57,000
you've grown into a young woman.

408
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:58,799
Look.

409
00:21:58,799 --> 00:22:00,480
This was the first certificate you won

410
00:22:00,559 --> 00:22:02,079
back in kindergarten.

411
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:04,640
You looked up at me and said,

412
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:06,480
"Mom,

413
00:22:06,799 --> 00:22:08,720
I'm going to win
every certificate in the world

414
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:10,880
and give them all to you."

415
00:22:11,839 --> 00:22:14,039
Do you still remember this certificate?

416
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:24,680
It's fine.

417
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:26,720
Eat up.

418
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:41,720
Yuci.

419
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:45,480
I came here today

420
00:22:49,079 --> 00:22:50,599
to apologize to you.

421
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:55,359
I was the one

422
00:22:55,359 --> 00:22:57,480
who brought you into this world,

423
00:22:59,279 --> 00:23:01,319
but I failed to protect you

424
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:06,799
and let you suffer so much harm.

425
00:23:09,599 --> 00:23:11,359
I've let you down.

426
00:23:19,279 --> 00:23:19,880
Calm down.

427
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:21,319
- My child!
- Calm down.

428
00:23:21,319 --> 00:23:22,640
(Three years ago)
Mrs. Rao, please calm down.

429
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:24,039
Calm down.

430
00:23:24,079 --> 00:23:26,240
Please calm down, Mrs. Rao.

431
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,680
Calm down.

432
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,920
No! Let go of me!

433
00:23:31,839 --> 00:23:33,240
Actually, every Thursday,

434
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:35,079
I would bring you

435
00:23:35,079 --> 00:23:36,400
your favorite dishes.

436
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,359
But the doctor said

437
00:23:38,839 --> 00:23:40,319
he was afraid seeing me

438
00:23:40,559 --> 00:23:42,880
would trigger your extreme emotions.

439
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:45,200
So I didn't dare

440
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:47,240
to see you face-to-face.

441
00:23:49,559 --> 00:23:50,880
Mr. Rao, I'm back.

442
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:51,599
Liangliang.

443
00:23:57,839 --> 00:23:58,640
Mrs. Rao.

444
00:23:58,960 --> 00:23:59,759
Mrs. Rao.

445
00:23:59,759 --> 00:24:00,559
Liangliang.

446
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:02,920
Liangliang, how was it?

447
00:24:03,039 --> 00:24:04,400
Did you see Yuci?

448
00:24:04,519 --> 00:24:05,720
I've arranged everything.

449
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:07,119
We'll go together next week.

450
00:24:07,119 --> 00:24:08,480
Is she much better?

451
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:09,799
Is that why she can see me now?

452
00:24:09,799 --> 00:24:11,200
Is she getting used to being there?

453
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,480
Mrs. Rao, don't get excited.

454
00:24:12,599 --> 00:24:14,160
Your health is the priority.

455
00:24:18,839 --> 00:24:22,599
I really blame myself.

456
00:24:24,519 --> 00:24:26,200
Bai Liangliang did so many things

457
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,559
to hurt you

458
00:24:27,839 --> 00:24:28,720
and intentionally

459
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,240
drove a wedge between us.

460
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:32,920
And I didn't even know.

461
00:24:35,039 --> 00:24:36,359
Yuci.

462
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:39,720
Mom.

463
00:24:53,599 --> 00:24:54,519
Mrs. Rao.

464
00:24:58,400 --> 00:24:59,240
Yuci.

465
00:25:09,799 --> 00:25:10,400
Yuci.

466
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:11,599
I can't see her.

467
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:13,240
I'll hurt her.

468
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,680
Yuci, it's me, your mom.

469
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:19,839
Yuci...

470
00:25:19,839 --> 00:25:21,359
It's me, your mom.

471
00:25:24,519 --> 00:25:27,440
I don't blame you, Yuci.

472
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:37,559
Can you forgive me?

473
00:25:40,039 --> 00:25:41,599
I was just too weak

474
00:25:41,599 --> 00:25:42,880
and incompetent.

475
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:00,799
I was wrong.

476
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:02,319
Truly, I was wrong.

477
00:26:02,319 --> 00:26:03,599
I'm so sorry.

478
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:09,599
Can you forgive me?

479
00:26:18,559 --> 00:26:19,359
Mom.

480
00:26:22,759 --> 00:26:24,079
My daughter.

481
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:28,880
Yuci, let's go home.

482
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,480
Things will get better, Yuci.

483
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:42,480
Let's go home.

484
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:57,319
Come, Yuci.

485
00:26:57,839 --> 00:26:58,920
Welcome home.

486
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:17,119
I've been so negligent.

487
00:27:17,359 --> 00:27:18,400
Chen told me

488
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,880
to check everything properly,

489
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:21,480
but I still forgot.

490
00:27:22,319 --> 00:27:23,279
Where is he?

491
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:24,680
He...

492
00:27:26,519 --> 00:27:28,000
He's still in a coma.

493
00:27:43,079 --> 00:27:45,240
No rush, take it slow.

494
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,279
You're much better.

495
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:51,599
The doctor said

496
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,880
as long as you take the medicine

497
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:53,880
and do the rehab on time,

498
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:55,359
you will definitely get better.

499
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:58,279
Neither of us should give up.

500
00:28:01,759 --> 00:28:02,559
Okay.

501
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:08,039
Mom.

502
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:11,799
Liangliang?

503
00:28:15,319 --> 00:28:16,359
I'm back.

504
00:28:18,319 --> 00:28:20,920
Mr. Xu, I'm back.

505
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:22,960
Mom,

506
00:28:23,599 --> 00:28:24,960
I'll take you

507
00:28:25,300 --> 00:28:26,759
to change the name on the title deed

508
00:28:26,759 --> 00:28:28,359
for No. 88 Linwei Alley tomorrow.

509
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:33,880
From now on, our family

510
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:36,039
will live a good life together.

511
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:40,240
Really?

512
00:28:44,279 --> 00:28:45,079
Yes.

513
00:28:49,119 --> 00:28:51,000
Liangliang, you're back.

514
00:28:53,839 --> 00:28:54,640
Good.

515
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:57,000
From now on, our family

516
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:59,680
will live a good life together.

517
00:29:54,359 --> 00:29:55,920
Master, wake up!

518
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,200
What's wrong?

519
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:58,839
Don't scare me.

520
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:01,119
Here.

521
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:03,240
Yuci.

522
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:06,039
You need to go see him.

523
00:30:06,039 --> 00:30:08,079
It'll be too late
if you wait any longer.

524
00:30:08,079 --> 00:30:10,559
We're running out of time.

525
00:30:32,359 --> 00:30:34,359
I'm suffocating.

526
00:30:35,759 --> 00:30:37,759
You put the nasal cannula in your mouth

527
00:30:37,759 --> 00:30:39,799
and stuck the chest lead on your head.

528
00:30:39,799 --> 00:30:41,200
How did you even come up with that?

529
00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:42,119
See?

530
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:43,640
I told you there was a problem.

531
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:44,759
You guys said it was fine.

532
00:30:44,759 --> 00:30:45,799
We were exposed instantly.

533
00:30:45,799 --> 00:30:46,759
How embarrassing.

534
00:30:46,759 --> 00:30:47,799
You agreed to it.

535
00:30:47,799 --> 00:30:49,160
Then, why didn't you object?

536
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:49,960
I just go with the flow.

537
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:50,559
You go with the flow?

538
00:30:50,559 --> 00:30:51,480
Stop.

539
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:53,880
How old are you?

540
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:55,500
Still playing these games?

541
00:30:56,160 --> 00:30:58,079
Who told you to always scare us?

542
00:30:58,319 --> 00:30:59,119
Right.

543
00:30:59,519 --> 00:31:00,680
So, we're letting you

544
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:01,880
taste your own medicine.

545
00:31:03,079 --> 00:31:04,079
You three rascals.

546
00:31:04,079 --> 00:31:04,759
That's right.

547
00:31:05,920 --> 00:31:07,559
We're the "Three Rascals" team.

548
00:31:09,640 --> 00:31:10,480
Childish.

549
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:14,440
Don't you ever play this kind
of joke on us again.

550
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:15,799
It was terrifying.

551
00:31:15,920 --> 00:31:17,279
The same goes for you.

552
00:31:19,119 --> 00:31:21,270
We didn't expect you
to be even crazier than we are.

553
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:25,119
Are you better now?

554
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:26,799
I'm better.

555
00:31:27,599 --> 00:31:28,880
Then, have you thought

556
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:30,119
about what you want to do next?

557
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:35,920
Rao Yuci, after you're discharged,

558
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:37,200
what are your plans?

559
00:31:38,519 --> 00:31:39,720
No matter what happens,

560
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:42,160
don't go back to Lysen.

561
00:31:42,279 --> 00:31:44,440
Don't go back to Lysen, Rao Yuci.

562
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:47,160
Look, I...

563
00:31:47,279 --> 00:31:48,480
I finally managed

564
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:50,160
to take charge of Dept 2 and 3.

565
00:31:50,300 --> 00:31:51,440
Even if it's just temporary,

566
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:52,880
I'll have my day
to shine sooner or later.

567
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:54,279
If you come back now,

568
00:31:55,279 --> 00:31:56,640
where am I supposed to sit?

569
00:32:04,279 --> 00:32:06,000
I guess that joke didn't land today.

570
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,640
Take my advice, okay?

571
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:09,960
People...

572
00:32:13,250 --> 00:32:14,680
People can't always live in the past,

573
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:16,240
always living in the shadows.

574
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:17,759
You can't carry

575
00:32:17,759 --> 00:32:18,799
too much on your shoulders.

576
00:32:18,799 --> 00:32:19,839
You'll exhaust yourself.

577
00:32:20,319 --> 00:32:21,759
It's nice to fall in love.

578
00:32:23,119 --> 00:32:24,160
As your friend,

579
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:26,680
I give Dr. Chen a perfect score.

580
00:32:27,599 --> 00:32:28,799
Live for yourself.

581
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,000
Okay?

582
00:32:42,599 --> 00:32:44,640
Next, whether you're willing or not,

583
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:46,759
you'll be swept up in all of this.

584
00:32:48,119 --> 00:32:49,160
Not just you,

585
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:53,200
but the people you care about around you

586
00:32:53,799 --> 00:32:55,920
will also be swept up in it.

587
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:24,160
(I spent decades)

588
00:33:24,880 --> 00:33:26,079
(struggling to crawl out)

589
00:33:26,079 --> 00:33:27,400
(from the quagmire step by step.)

590
00:33:29,799 --> 00:33:31,400
(This Lysen I've painstakingly built...)

591
00:33:33,279 --> 00:33:34,079
(No one)

592
00:33:34,839 --> 00:33:36,240
(can kick me out of the game.)

593
00:33:37,319 --> 00:33:40,240
(Lysen Group Annual Shareholder Appreciation Event)
Welcome to

594
00:33:40,279 --> 00:33:42,480
the Lysen Group Shareholder
Appreciation Event.

595
00:33:42,519 --> 00:33:45,440
Please welcome Mr. Jiang Dongchao
with a round of applause!

596
00:33:55,519 --> 00:33:58,640
(The Day It All Began)
Today is our Lysen's

597
00:33:58,640 --> 00:33:59,920
Shareholder Appreciation Event.

598
00:34:01,759 --> 00:34:03,079
According to our tradition,

599
00:34:03,359 --> 00:34:04,440
I should first talk

600
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:05,720
about the story behind Lysen.

601
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:07,799
It's the same every year,
never changing.

602
00:34:08,039 --> 00:34:09,159
I'm sure you

603
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:11,800
must be tired of hearing it.

604
00:34:12,719 --> 00:34:13,519
So,

605
00:34:14,239 --> 00:34:16,280
today I am going to break that routine.

606
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:18,599
I'd like to share with you

607
00:34:19,199 --> 00:34:20,400
a story about a man

608
00:34:22,159 --> 00:34:23,559
and a woman.

609
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:33,719
We were university classmates,

610
00:34:34,519 --> 00:34:35,760
both majoring in

611
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:37,199
English Language and Literature.

612
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:39,039
But our story

613
00:34:39,280 --> 00:34:41,079
unfolded like a piece of literature.

614
00:34:41,519 --> 00:34:43,360
Meeting, getting to know each other...

615
00:34:43,519 --> 00:34:44,760
It's Dad.

616
00:34:44,760 --> 00:34:46,160
Going abroad together to work hard,

617
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:47,880
and walking into marriage hand-in-hand.

618
00:34:50,159 --> 00:34:51,159
It's Dad.

619
00:34:52,559 --> 00:34:53,679
I saw it.

620
00:34:53,679 --> 00:34:54,840
Just as I was about to reach

621
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:56,400
the peak of my life,

622
00:34:57,719 --> 00:34:58,800
the doctor told me

623
00:34:59,519 --> 00:35:00,480
that my wife

624
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:03,880
had cancer.

625
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:06,519
After knowing that,

626
00:35:07,599 --> 00:35:08,880
I didn't sleep for days.

627
00:35:17,380 --> 00:35:20,900
=Episode 18=
(The Return)

628
00:35:21,540 --> 00:35:23,980
(All animals in this production
were treated humanely)

629
00:35:23,980 --> 00:35:30,180
♪Take a breath and swallow
the words you couldn't say♪

630
00:35:30,940 --> 00:35:34,140
♪No need to force your heart anymore♪

631
00:35:34,140 --> 00:35:38,660
♪Searching for the season
we once missed♪

632
00:35:38,660 --> 00:35:46,180
♪Leave this place,
though wounded still stay strong♪

633
00:35:46,180 --> 00:35:50,100
♪You must believe
one day the rain will fall♪

634
00:35:50,100 --> 00:35:54,140
♪And wash away the mud
that stains your soul♪

635
00:35:54,140 --> 00:35:57,660
♪Find your freedom in the wild♪

636
00:35:57,660 --> 00:36:01,620
♪Take your stride and move ahead♪

637
00:36:01,620 --> 00:36:05,780
♪I will stay behind
and wait for your eyes♪

638
00:36:05,780 --> 00:36:09,980
♪To rebuild
the same flesh and soul again♪

639
00:36:09,980 --> 00:36:13,780
♪Wander freely through the thorns♪

640
00:36:13,780 --> 00:36:17,860
♪Keep walking through the light♪

641
00:36:17,860 --> 00:36:22,060
♪Fate is absurd, don't stop for anyone♪

642
00:36:22,060 --> 00:36:28,380
♪What you dare to lose
will one day be your own♪

643
00:36:45,500 --> 00:36:52,140
♪I'm sorry, I still owe you these words♪

644
00:36:52,140 --> 00:36:55,980
♪An apology that came too late♪

645
00:36:55,980 --> 00:37:00,620
♪Yet it's also the path
that saves my soul♪

646
00:37:00,700 --> 00:37:08,100
♪When the cold wind
passes it takes the past away♪

647
00:37:08,100 --> 00:37:12,180
♪You must believe and stand unwavering♪

648
00:37:12,180 --> 00:37:16,260
♪There will be hands
to pull you from the deep♪

649
00:37:16,260 --> 00:37:20,260
♪Find your freedom in the silence♪

650
00:37:20,260 --> 00:37:24,020
♪Let your wounds be mended♪

651
00:37:24,020 --> 00:37:28,220
♪Gray is not the past
and pain is not a shame♪

652
00:37:28,220 --> 00:37:32,380
♪Sometimes the sunlight
makes the world look crueler♪

653
00:37:32,380 --> 00:37:36,100
♪Wander through the echoes of regret♪

654
00:37:36,100 --> 00:37:40,140
♪Be forgiven and be sheltered♪

655
00:37:40,140 --> 00:37:44,180
♪After everything shatters,
hold my hand♪

656
00:37:44,180 --> 00:37:50,380
♪A flower reborn
will finally bloom forever♪
